---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";

const frontmatter = {
	title: "Documentation",
	order: 0,
};
---

<DocsLayout frontmatter={frontmatter}>
    <h1
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold text-white tracking-tighter text-balance mb-12"
    >
        Dione Documentation
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p>
            Welcome to the official documentation for Dione, the open-source platform that makes it easy to discover, install, and manage AI applications.
        </p>

        <p>
            Whether you're a new user looking to get started or a developer interested in contributing, you'll find everything you need right here.
        </p>

        <h2>What is Dione?</h2>
        <p>
            Dione is a one-click installer for AI applications. It simplifies the process of finding, downloading, and running a wide range of open-source AI tools. With Dione, you can spend less time on setup and more time exploring the exciting world of AI.
        </p>

        <h2>How to Use These Docs</h2>
        <p>
            This documentation is organized into several sections, accessible via the sidebar on the left.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Getting Started:</strong> If you're new to Dione, this is the place to begin. It covers installation and initial setup.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>User Guide:</strong> Learn how to use Dione's features, from exploring and installing apps to running them.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Developer Guide:</strong> For those who want to contribute to Dione or add their own apps to the platform.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Troubleshooting:</strong> Find solutions to common issues you might encounter.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            We recommend starting with the <a href="/getting-started/installation">Installation</a> guide.
        </p>
    </div>
</DocsLayout>
